<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Expect on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/expect/</link><description>Recent content in Expect on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/expect/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ Google Test - assertion error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/gtest-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/gtest-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="google-test---assertion-error"&gt;Google Test - assertion error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Google Test assertion errors are reported by EXPECT_* and ASSERT_* macros when conditions are not met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: EXPECT_* failure (non-fatal)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_EQ(a, b); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// logs failure but continues
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: ASSERT_* failure (fatal)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ASSERT_NE(ptr, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;nullptr&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// stops current test
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Floating point comparison
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_EQ(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.3&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// fails due to precision
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-correct-comparison"&gt;Fix 1: Use correct comparison&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// For floating point
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_NEAR(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0.3&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1e-9&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// For containers
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_THAT(vec, testing&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ElementsAre(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-add-failure-messages"&gt;Fix 2: Add failure messages&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; compute();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_EQ(result, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;compute() returned &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;, expected 42&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-death-tests-for-crashes"&gt;Fix 3: Use death tests for crashes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;EXPECT_DEATH(func_that_crashes(), &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;.*&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/catch2-error/"&gt;Catch2 - test error&lt;/a&gt; — Catch2 errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/doctest-error/"&gt;doctest - test error&lt;/a&gt; — doctest errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/boost-test-error/"&gt;Boost.Test - test error&lt;/a&gt; — Boost.Test errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Jest: Test Assertion Failed Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/jest-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/jest-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="jest-test-assertion-failed"&gt;Jest: Test Assertion Failed&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a Jest test&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;expect()&lt;/code&gt; assertion does not match the expected value. It indicates a mismatch between what the code produces and what the test expects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common error messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect(received).toEqual(expected): Expected equality&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect(received).toBeDefined(): Received undefined&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect(received).toHaveLength(3): Received length 0&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect(received).rejects.toThrow(): Didn't throw&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;Snapshot mismatch&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jest compares actual values against expected values. When the comparison fails, Jest shows a diff between received and expected values.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin Expect/Actual Mismatch Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/expect-actual-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/expect-actual-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An expect/actual mismatch error occurs when an expect declaration does not have a matching actual implementation in all target platforms. Kotlin Multiplatform uses expect/actual for platform-specific code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing actual declaration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Signature mismatch between expect and actual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong platform target&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing dependency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Missing actual declaration
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Platform&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getName&lt;/span&gt;(): String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// No actual implementation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Provide actual implementation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// commonMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Platform&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getName&lt;/span&gt;(): String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// androidMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Platform&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;constructor&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getName&lt;/span&gt;(): String = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Android&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// iosMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Platform&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;constructor&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getName&lt;/span&gt;(): String = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;iOS&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Signature mismatch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getPlatformName&lt;/span&gt;(): String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getPlatformName&lt;/span&gt;(): Int &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong return type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Match signatures
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getPlatformName&lt;/span&gt;(): String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getPlatformName&lt;/span&gt;(): String = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Android&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-kotlin" data-lang="kotlin"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Platform class
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Navigator&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;navigateTo&lt;/span&gt;(url: String)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// androidMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Navigator&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;navigateTo&lt;/span&gt;(url: String) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Android implementation
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Platform function
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getCurrentTime&lt;/span&gt;(): Long
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// androidMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getCurrentTime&lt;/span&gt;(): Long = &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;System&lt;/span&gt;.currentTimeMillis()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: Platform constant
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;expect&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; PLATFORM_NAME: String
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// androidMain
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;actual&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;val&lt;/span&gt; PLATFORM_NAME: String = &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Android&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="inline-reified-error"&gt;Inline reified error&lt;/a&gt; — reified type issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="contract-error"&gt;Contracts error&lt;/a&gt; — contracts issue&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="gradle-kotlin-dsl-error"&gt;Gradle Kotlin DSL error&lt;/a&gt; — Gradle error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Called expect on Err — Expect Panic on Result</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/expect-fail-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/expect-fail-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="called-expect-on-err--expect-panic-on-result"&gt;Called expect on Err — Expect Panic on Result&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;called &lt;code&gt;Result::expect()&lt;/code&gt; on an &lt;code&gt;Err&lt;/code&gt; value: &amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo; occurs when you call &lt;code&gt;.expect()&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;code&gt;Result&lt;/code&gt; that contains an &lt;code&gt;Err&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect()&lt;/code&gt; works identically to &lt;code&gt;unwrap()&lt;/code&gt; but accepts a custom message string that appears in the panic output. It documents &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; the programmer believes the operation should succeed. Despite the better error message, &lt;code&gt;.expect()&lt;/code&gt; still panics — the distinction from &lt;code&gt;.unwrap()&lt;/code&gt; is diagnostic, not behavioral.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Called expect on Err — Result Expect Panic</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/expect-fail/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/expect-fail/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="called-expect-on-err--result-expect-panic"&gt;Called expect on Err — Result Expect Panic&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;called &lt;code&gt;Result::expect()&lt;/code&gt; on an &lt;code&gt;Err&lt;/code&gt; value: &amp;hellip;&amp;rdquo; occurs when you call &lt;code&gt;.expect()&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;code&gt;Result&lt;/code&gt; that contains an &lt;code&gt;Err&lt;/code&gt;. Unlike &lt;code&gt;.unwrap()&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;.expect()&lt;/code&gt; allows you to provide a custom panic message, but the panic behavior is identical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;expect()&lt;/code&gt; is similar to &lt;code&gt;unwrap()&lt;/code&gt; but takes a message string that is included in the panic output. It&amp;rsquo;s meant to document &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; the unwrap is believed to be safe. When the result is &lt;code&gt;Err&lt;/code&gt;, the custom message and the underlying error are both displayed. While more informative than &lt;code&gt;unwrap()&lt;/code&gt;, it still panics — which may be inappropriate for recoverable errors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>